<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76964" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-745x497.jpg" alt="Custom Triumph Street Twin by MFix Workshop" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
<span class="lede">They say that</span> if you customize your motorcycle, you&#8217;re married to it. We&#8217;re going to go out on a limb and say that that&#8217;s even truer if your custom job includes a reggae-themed paint job. But that&#8217;s exactly what the owner of this custom Triumph Street Twin asked for, so that&#8217;s exactly what Vietnam&#8217;s MFix Workshop delivered.</p>
<p>Ironically, this <em>irie</em> Triumph boasts a pretty gnarly spec sheet. MFix&#8217;s client is not only a fan of reggae music, but he&#8217;s a long-time dirt bike rider too. So although the colors suit his laid-back vibe, this <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/tag/street-tracker" target="_blank" rel="noopener">street tracker</a> is configured for enthusiastic shenanigans.<span id="more-76957"></span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76962" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-745x497.jpg" alt="Custom Triumph Street Twin by MFix Workshop" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-1.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
His first request was for a full suite of <a href="https://motogadget.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Motogadget</a> electronics with smartphone integration—so that&#8217;s where MFix started. With the bike stripped of its OEM wiring loom, the crew installed a Bluetooth-enabled Motogadget mo.unit controller and built the new system up from there. They also added a lightweight Lithium-ion battery, and a special box from Peak-Mod that allows you to bypass the Triumph&#8217;s notoriously tricky electronics to run an aftermarket speedo.</p>
<p>Everything is packaged neatly under the seat, kept in check by alternating red, yellow, and green cable ties. Going deeper, MFix upgraded the engine with a new camshaft from TEC, a Dynojet Power Commander 6 ECU, heavy-duty EBS clutch plates, and a smattering of other sneaky performance-enhancing items. They also nixed the Street Twin&#8217;s emissions sensors to help it breathe easier.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76966" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-745x497.jpg" alt="Custom Triumph Street Twin by MFix Workshop" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-2.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Next, all of the Street Twin&#8217;s running gear went in the bin. MFix fitted a set of adjustable Öhlins FG 621 forks to the front end, along with CNC-machined yokes and a Matris steering damper. The aluminum swingarm from a Triumph Thruxton R does duty out back, hooked up to a pair of adjustable K-Tech Razor shocks.</p>
<p>The new suspension is not only a massive upgrade over the stock setup but it&#8217;s given the Street Twin a more respectable ride height too. The new 19F/17R wheels come from Kineo, with Metzeler Tourance tires offering great street grip with just a hint of gravel ability. Brembo Serie Oro brake calipers keep things sensible, while a Triumph Scrambler 1200 side stand caters for the increased ground clearance.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76967" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-745x497.jpg" alt="Custom Triumph Street Twin by MFix Workshop" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-3.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Moving to the bodywork, MFix shortened the Street Twin&#8217;s subframe and covered it with a hand-made composite flat track tail section. Topped off with a leather seat, it&#8217;s a perfect match for the Triumph&#8217;s stock fuel tank.</p>
<p>A powerful LED headlight and enduro-style cowl from Rigid adorn the front of the bike, floating above a custom split mudguard design and flat track-style fork protectors. Further back you&#8217;ll find a bespoke MFix Performance radiator and an Evotech skid plate. Custom aluminum side panels complete the set.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76968" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-745x497.jpg" alt="Custom Triumph Street Twin by MFix Workshop" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-5.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
The Triumph&#8217;s cockpit is all-new too. Custom risers hold wide Domino flat track handlebars, while the top clamp doubles up as a mounting point for a tiny Motogadget speedo. The hydraulic brake and clutch controls are from Brembo; the latter is hooked up to an Adelin hydraulic clutch slave cylinder.</p>
<p>Other Motogadget bits include the keyless ignition, mini switches, turn signals, and taillights. MX-style grips add another splash of color, while a single rear-view mirror keeps the fuzz at bay.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76969" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-745x497.jpg" alt="Custom Triumph Street Twin by MFix Workshop" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-6.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
From there on out, MFix&#8217;s job was to style this custom Triumph Street Twin according to their client&#8217;s requests—which went beyond just the Rastafari-inspired livery. Because he&#8217;s a big fan of the classic Yamaha SR400, he requested a pair of special engine badges that pay homage to it. One reads &#8216;SR900&#8217; and the other &#8216;SR400/500,&#8217; both in reference to the Street Twin&#8217;s 900 cc engine.</p>
<p>He also specified the lime green Acerbis heat shield that&#8217;s mounted to the burly two-into-one Zard exhaust system.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76970" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-745x497.jpg" alt="Custom Triumph Street Twin by MFix Workshop" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/custom-triumph-street-twin-7.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
The chaotic color scheme and retina-searing highlights certainly won&#8217;t appeal to everyone—but MFix didn&#8217;t build this bike for everyone. Besides, it&#8217;s hard to argue with an everyday street bike that&#8217;s this well-specced.</p>
